@node QUOI "What's Post-It ?"
   Post-It is a small program but a very useful one.Post It can appear messages on the
Workbench's screen when a date is reached.So it can be very useful when you have to
remember to do something one day.Post-It is a sort of mini organiser.

                                    @{"Return to the menu" LINK MAIN}
@endnode
@node BESOIN "What are the requirements of Post-It v2.1 ?"
   This is the list of the requirements :
      - An Amiga of course ! (I don't know if Post-It works on all Amigas)
      - The Workbench (I think at least the Workbench 2.0)
      - Some memory (I don't know how many but I think it's in the fifties kb...)
      - Some spaces on the drawers S: and C:
      - A clock (present on the accelerator cards)
      - The program Ed in C: (Ed is giving with the Workbench)
      - The font Oil-Imp with a height of 12 in the drawer FONTS:

   Caution ! If you don't have a thing of the requirements' list,in most cases,the
             Amiga will crash !

   Post-It has been only tested on an Amiga 1200 with the Workbench 3.0 in 704 x 536 x 4,
with a card Mtec 68030 28 Mhz 8 Mb of Fast ram,a Cd-Rom x4,an Hard Disk of 700 Mb :
Post-It works fine !

                                    @{"Return to the menu" LINK MAIN}
@endnode
