@node MARCHE "How to use this fucking program ?!!!"
   We can use Post-It by 2 way : by the Cli (or by Shell) or by the Workbench

   --> By the Workbench <--

      Double-click on the icon of Post-It to run it.If all is ok, a window call
     "Post It It v2.1 * Gugu Best *" will appear on the Workbench's screen : you're
     in Post-It

   --> By the Cli <--

      Here there is the synopsis for the Cli : Post-It <option>
                                           or  Post-It <day> <month> <year>
                                           or simply  Post-It

         In the first case, <option> can be "close"
               example: Post-It close
            The "close" option close Post-It when there aren't messages for the current
            date.
            In this version, there is only 1 option but maybe the future versions will
            have more...

         In the 2nd case, Post-It display the message of the date <day>/<month>/<year>
               example: Post-It 10 09 1998
                  This example display the message for the date 10/09/1998.
                  Note: 1998 can be write 98
                        <day> <month> and <year> must be numbers.

         In the last case, Post-It is run without any options.

                                    @{"Return to the menu" LINK MAIN}
@endnode
@node INTERFACE "The interface of Post-It..."
   The interface of Post-it is very easy, there are two parts : the actions' part which
it is on the top of the Post-it's window and the messages' part which it is on the bottom of
the window.

      * The actions' part
         There are 4 gadgets : edit,delete,view day and quit.
          Click on :
            - "Edit" to @{"edit the messages" LINK EDITER} with Ed.
            - "Delete" to kill the current message.
            - "View day" to select a day.
            - "Quit" to quit Pos-It.Note: you can also type ESC key.

      * The messages' part...
         First,there is the date : example : date 01/09/98 and after,there is the
         message (when there is one) for this date.

                                    @{"Return to the menu" LINK MAIN}
@endnode
@node EDITER "How to edit the messages..."
   The messages are in a ASCII text file.The path of this file is : S:post_it.data
If you have used the gadget "Edit" of the interface of Post-It,Ed will be already in
this file.
   To write messages, you must type in this file :
      * <day>/<month>/<year>
         <message.....................................................
         .............................................................
         .............................................................>

      Change <day> <month> and <year> by the date which do you want your <message> to be
      display on.
         NOTE: <message> can't be superior at 10 lines !!!!!!
      If you don't understand,see this example :

      * 01/09/98
      Hello the world !!!
      Cool ! no ?
      * 24/12/98
      Happy Chritsmas !!
      * 01/01/99
      Good year !!

      etc...It's all ! I hope you understood how to write a message.

                                    @{"Return to the menu" LINK MAIN}

@endnode
@node PROBLEMES "Have you got a problem ?"
   Here there are the problems what you can have :

      1- Post-It doesn't appear his window when it's run.
          -Verify if you have run Post-It on an Amiga and not on Pc or Mac.
          -If you have run it by the Cli,are you sure what you don't have put the
           "close" option ?(for more informations,click @{"here" LINK MARCHE}
          -Are you sure you have @{"all the requirements" LINK BESOIN} ?

      2- The Amiga crashs after you run Post-It.
          -Verify if you have @{"all the requirements" LINK BESOIN}.
          -You can have an incompactible Amiga or the Workbench is incompactible with Post-It,
           In this case,say it to me by @{"mail" LINK CONTACT}.
          -Rerun Post-It to see if it works.

      3- The Amiga explode after you run Post-It.
          -Fuck your dealer !!
          -It's not the fault of Post-It.

      4- I don't have the problems mentioned.
          -Verify if you have problems.
          -If you have one,@{"contact me" LINK CONTACT}

                                    @{"Return to the menu" LINK MAIN}
@endnode
